  "response": "The number of books an average person reads in a year can vary widely depending on factors like age, culture, and reading habits. However, surveys and studies suggest that on average, many adults read about 12 books per year, while the median number tends to be lower, around 4 books per year. \n\nIt's important to note that these numbers can fluctuate based on personal preferences, lifestyle, and access to books. Some individuals might read significantly more, while others may not read at all.",
